WEBVTT

00:14.600 --> 00:22.640
VIII. And when he had opened the seventh seal, there was silence in heaven about the space

00:22.640 --> 00:24.220
of half an hour.

00:25.800 --> 00:32.200
And I saw the seven angels which stood before God, and to them were given seven trumpets.

00:32.560 --> 00:39.040
And another angel came and stood at the altar, having a golden censer, and there was given unto

00:39.040 --> 00:45.380
him much incense that he should offer it with the prayers of all saints, upon the golden altar which

00:45.380 --> 00:50.740
was before the throne. And the smoke of the incense which came with the prayers of the saints

00:50.740 --> 00:57.400
ascended up before God out of the angel's hand. And the angel took the censer and filled it with

00:57.400 --> 01:03.460
fire of the altar and cast it into the earth. And there were voices and thunderings and

01:03.460 --> 01:09.620
lightnings and an earthquake. And the seven angels which had the seven trumpets prepared

01:09.620 --> 01:16.980
themselves to sound. The first angel sounded, and there followed hail and fire mingled with blood,

01:16.980 --> 01:23.620
and they were cast upon the earth. And the third part of trees was burnt up, and all green grass

01:23.620 --> 01:30.820
was burnt up. And the second angel sounded. And as it were a great mountain burning with fire was

01:30.820 --> 01:37.240
cast into the sea, and the third part of the sea became blood. And the third part of the creatures

01:37.240 --> 01:43.840
which were in the sea and had life died. And the third part of the ships were destroyed. And the

01:43.840 --> 01:50.280
third angel sounded. And there fell a great star from heaven burning as it were a lamp. And it fell

01:50.280 --> 01:56.620
upon the third part of the rivers and upon the fountains of waters. And the name of the star is

01:56.620 --> 02:03.940
called Wormwood. And the third part of the waters became Wormwood. And many men died of the waters

02:03.940 --> 02:09.680
because they were made bitter. And the fourth angel sounded. And the third part of the sun was

02:09.680 --> 02:15.720
smitten, and the third part of the moon, and the third part of the stars. So as the third part of

02:15.720 --> 02:22.280
them was darkened, and the day shone not for a third part of it, and the night likewise. And I

02:22.280 --> 02:27.660
beheld and heard an angel flying through the midst of heaven, saying with a loud voice,

02:28.980 --> 02:34.760
Woe, woe, woe to the inhabiters of the earth by reason of the other voices of the trumpet of

02:34.760 --> 02:41.120
three angels which are yet to sound. The end of chapter 8.

